		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thanks for the reply <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":-)" title="Smile" />
<br />
<br />As you said when the channel is turned off it outputs 0v (silence). So when its shift is set to 4 then then it passes 0 to the dac which is -1v. This isnt silence yet the gameboy snd wiki says that shifting 4 outputs silence.

		

		</td>
